cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI. 

The paper discusses distributed detection and estimation algorithms in wireless sensor networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.MA), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on optimizing network topology also suggests a potential fit with the cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) sub-category. However, given the emphasis on communication constraints and statistical dependencies, we believe the other five categories are more likely.
